dcterms:description: UTDAC2020 is one of the series dataset from Underwater Target Detection Algorithm Competition 2020. It contains 5,168 training images and 1,293 validation images with 4 classes: echinus, holothurian, starfish, and scallop. The images in the dataset have 4 resolutions: 3840 × 2160, 1920 × 1080, 720 × 405, and 586 × 480.
dcterms:title: UTDAC2020

dcterms:description: TrashCan dataset comes from the J-EDI deepsea image electronic library managed by the Japan Agency of Marine Earth Science and Technology (JAMSTEC). It contains 1,000 video data of different lengths from various sea areas in Japan, labeled with two versions: TrashCan-Instance and TrashCan-Material. The TrashCan-Material version contains 16 object categories such as trash, rov, bio, unknown, metal, and plastic, with 6,008 training images and 1,204 validation images.
dcterms:title: TrashCan

dcterms:description: Brackish is the first annotated underwater image dataset captured in temperate brackish waters. It contains 6 classes: bigfish, crab, jellyfish, shrimp, small fish, and starfish, with a total of 14,518 frames and 25,613 annotations. The dataset is manually annotated with a bounding box annotation tool and is split into training, validation, and test sets.
dcterms:title: Brackish
